cs.RO, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper is about reproducibility and sharing of experimental artifacts in robotics research. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel experimental workflow to describe, execute and distribute experimental software-artifacts. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses operating-system-level virtualization to isolate experimental artifacts in containers that can be distributed to other researchers. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the complexity of robotics and proposes a solution to support researchers in executing and reproducing experimental evaluations. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on programming languages specifically, but rather on the reproducibility and sharing of experimental artifacts in robotics research.
